dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Creates rasters based on daily gridded surface data mosaicked across tiles. The tool converts yearly daymet NetCDF file for a daymet variable to multiple rasters in the TIFF format. Each raster represents daily value for the daymet variable and the raster is mosaicked for the specified tiles.

More information about the daymet data can be found at the daymet website.

tool.name: CreateDailyRasters

param.name: input_daymet_data_folder
param.dialogReference: The folder containing the daily gridded surface daymet data. One or more NetCDF files (with .nc file extension) from this folder are processed.

param.name: daymet_variable
param.expression: DAY_LENGTH | MAX_TEMPERATURE | MIN_TEMPERATURE | PRECIPITATION | SHORTWAVE_RADIATION | SNOW_WATER_EQUIVALENT | VAPOR_PRESSURE_DEFICIT
param.dialogReference:
The daymet variable you want to process. The output rasters will represent daily values for this variable. The parameter is specified as one of the following keywords representing a daymet variable.

  • DAY_LENGTH - Process daylength data from dayl.nc files.

  • MAX_TEMPERATURE - Process maximum temperature data from tmax.nc files.

  • MIN_TEMPERATURE - Process minimum temperature data from tmin.nc files.

  • PRECIPITATION - Process precipitation data from prcp.nc files.

  • SHORTWAVE_RADIATION - Process shortwave radiation data from srad.nc files.

  • SNOW_WATER_EQUIVALENT - Process snow-water equivalent data from swe.nc files.

  • VAPOR_PRESSURE_DEFICIT - Process vapor pressure deficit data from vp.nc files.

param.name: tiles_to_process
param.dialogReference: The tiles to process daymet files and produce mosiacked raster. The daymet file corresponding to the daymet variable for each of the selected tiles will be processed.

param.name: start_year
param.dialogReference: The starting year to select the daymet data for processing. All daymet files within the start and year years will be processed.

param.name: end_year
param.dialogReference: The ending year to select the daymet data for processing. All daymet files within the start and year years will be processed.

param.name: output_folder
param.dialogReference: The folder to contain the daily mosaicked rasters.

tool.summary:
Creates rasters based on daily gridded surface data mosaicked across tiles. The tool converts yearly daymet NetCDF file for a daymet variable to multiple rasters in the TIFF format. Each raster represents daily value for the daymet variable and the raster is mosaicked for the specified tiles.

More information about the daymet data can be found at the daymet website.
tool.usage:
• Each daymet file takes considerable time to process. The tool takes advantage of multiple CPU cores on the machine. It can utilize upto half of the CPU cores on the machine to process multiple files simultaneously and speed up the overall data processing. Running the tool on a machine with many CPU cores will improve the tool execution time.

  • The tool creates intermidiate rasters such as a raster representing all the bands from the daymet file and rasters for the individual bands. These intermidiate rasters are created in the output folder and are deleted as the final step during the tool execution.
